From the establishment and operation of this material docking platform, we can see the power of mutual assistance.
By Zhao Yenan
Editor | Luo Lixuan

On January 24, the 30th day of the Chinese New Year and the second day of the "city closure" in Wuhan.

With the flood of patients arriving at the hospital, all supplies were in short supply. On this day, hospitals in several Hubei cities, including Wuhan, regardless of possible "organizational" risks, they began to disperse into the streets: they needed goggles, protective clothing, surgical masks... anything that would keep them on the front lines.

In the face of calls for help from the front line, civil society is gathering strength, and volunteers from far and wide are linking up on the Internet and rapidly forming volunteer organizations with the same goal: to help the hospital, in whatever form.

Among them are a group of programmers who choose to use the skills and abilities they have mastered to help them live in the city. Haquet, Lao Peng and a Wei work in Wuhan Guanggu Software Park. Faced with the ever-increasing demand of hospitals and the lack of matching materials, they decided to establish a matching platform of medical materials information to improve the circulation of money and materials.

Up to now, already had a dozen friends to join together, organizing the operation of this platform. There are many more volunteers and donors involved. Everyone plays their part. They don't see each other, but they trust each other. They work together on the network to complete the construction and operation of this material docking platform.

This is a folk aid story that is taking place and taking place in this era.

A group of people who care about one thing

Xian Bai Hao is not in the mood to watch the Spring Festival gala, has been on the mobile phone brush Wuhan Epidemic Related News.

This is the fourth day that the news of COVID-19 pneumonia has been confirmed by Zhong Nanshan on CCTV. That night, he saw a group of friends who posted "refueling for Wuhan, " and he clicked on a Qr code to add it.

On the same day, dozens of hospitals, including the Wuhan Union Hospital, the Hubei Provincial People's Hospital and the Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, issued a public notice, appealing to all sectors of society to help. It's a lot of information, and a lot of people want to donate. Many secondhand hospital information and donation information are difficult to verify and complete the smooth docking.

That night, Bai Hao joined the group, and the discussion never stopped. Many people in the group forwarded the donation of these hospitals announcement, far and wide volunteers, whether in Wuhan or not, are in the group to discuss, hope to contribute.

Lao Peng, a native of Wuhan, has more pressing concerns. Lao Peng is a software engineer who works for a technology company in Guanggu Software Park.

"Light Valley" official name is the Donghu New Technology Development Zone, in 2001 by the former State Planning Commission, the Ministry of Science and Technology approved for the national optoelectronic industry base, thus obtaining the nickname: "China Light Valley. Today, it is the Internet hub of Wuhan, home to hundreds of high tech companies including Microsoft, Huawei, Xiaomi, Iflytek, and Xiaohongshu, as well as local innovators.

Since the city was sealed off on the 23rd, Lao Peng and his colleagues have isolated themselves at home, unable to go anywhere. "sealed off the city" the next day's supplies are in short supply, they all see in the eye. He and his colleagues in the company group discussed, feel can use his career to help them, make the material docking more efficient.

When Peng, who has designed and developed the project in his company's group, asked if it was feasible, they replied: Of course. Just after midnight on the 25th, he posted a friend's circle, hoping that more friends would join in and help.


People who saw the friend group pulled him and his colleagues to the volunteer group where Bai Hao was. Peng told the group that they could help set up an H5 form of information platform to facilitate the hospital's interface with donors. The friends in the group responded warmly and hoped that they could also help.

It was at this point that Bai Han took the initiative to add Lao Peng, trying to do his best to help. Over the course of the night, responsibilities were being rapidly assigned, and Baehan was immediately the media liaison for the information platform team.

That night, Kalopeng and his colleagues were in many heads -- "I'm a product manager in Beijing, I'm from Wuhan" "I can do Java, I graduated from Wuhan in 15 years" "I do UI design, I want to join" .

For a while, friends from different places came together through this event. They were both online friends and had never met. "We didn't know each other very well, but we came together quickly on this, " Baehan said.

By a little after 2:00 a.m. on the 25th, the basic staff structure had been completed. Lao Peng, Haquet, and a Wei, along with three colleagues from the company, became the main leaders in setting up the information platform. Haquet is in charge of technology, Peng is in charge of operations, and Wei is in charge of product design. "We expect to get the H5 up and running first tonight, " Peng said on facebook. "there will be a lot of typing work to do and help from everyone. " At the end, he said twice: "thank you very much. "

A few of them stayed up all night. By 10 a.m. on the 25th, in just over seven hours, the prototype of the docking platform had been set up. Click on this link to see the details of each of the hospitals that receive donations, including the hospital's address, contact number, list of requirements, standards of protective equipment and related pictures, you can also dial the number left by the hospital.

It's being updated every day

The quick-build platform facilitates the rapid interface between the hospital and the donor, and the information is verified, updated and the platform architecture iterated daily. Behind the platform, there are more friends with the same goal, who volunteer to take on different responsibilities, work hard for the operation of the platform, and extend the extension of the meaning of the platform's function in different groups.

A small organizational structure quickly takes shape. They set up a co-ordination group to carry out the division of labour and arrangements among the different responsibilities. Product team is responsible for front-end and back-end build and test, platform function iteration, operation team is responsible for hospital data collection, customer service team is responsible for hospital information verification, a call to the Hospital for verification; The hospital will also be in charge of pulling into a group, the need for docking and updating.

More and more friends have joined, and these "volunteers" are joining not only as individuals but also as companies.

They integrate the verification of hospital information using graphite documents to make it easy to add and modify. Graphite's office is next door to the company, which just a year ago raised nearly billion yuan from bytedance. Eager colleagues there soon contacted Haquet, offering them tech support and giving them free VIP access.

In order to ensure the accuracy of the information, Lao Peng and his team prioritized the information released by the hospital's official public number, micro blog and website, followed by the information released by the credible media, next is the hospital information forwarded by bloggers, from the media and so on.


Early on the morning of the 26th, platform 2.0 went live. Peng posted a platform message poster on his friends'circle.

After the update, the platform to the public open platform contact, more friends can understand the hospital information, donation information sent to the platform, after verification display. On the day of the interview, the hospital information on the platform is divided into "information verified" and a small number of "information not verified" status, which will be revised after the hospital information is verified.

"We don't want to doubt the needs of any of the hospitals, " Peng said. To ensure that no hospital in need is left out, a small number of hospitals whose information has not been verified will be put on the platform first, and then we can verify it step by step.

In the meantime, 2.0 also comes online with vehicle resource information. Including government vehicles, civilian volunteer vehicles and Logistics Company volunteer vehicles. Provide contact information, distribution scope, distribution time and other information, although some information is not perfect.

Each volunteer was busy doing his or her job, regardless of the reward. As a result of their efforts, the platform is updated every day, from front-end information to back-end technology.

To the later versions 3.0 and 4.0, the hospital display locations were prioritized by the number of hospital visits and contact times respectively; the security of the platform system and information were upgraded, and the background was encrypted, the source of each piece of data information can also be traced. Hospital Certification Letters, medical licensing, donation announcements are also added, from the heavy manual audit gradually become automated audit.

Today, version 4.0 of the platform is officially launched. As of today, the platform has reviewed 801 hospital information and 66 vehicle resource information. At the same time, their organization has continued to grow, incorporating many other volunteer organizations. Together, they named this temporary gathering of Public Welfare Organizations "E-qi support" , hoping to represent the spirit of interconnection and mutual assistance.

Other public welfare organisations that have merged with the "e-support" initiative

Bai said many hospitals have received much-needed material donations through the platform, including many Chinese and businesses at home and abroad. And the docking is still ongoing.

Tired, questioning and moved

These days, Bai Han and Lao Peng, many of these volunteers did not sleep well.

Since the day he got involved, Peng has been sleeping only two or three hours a day. Old Peng's family and friends all feel a little sorry for him. Especially the family, "they think I'm too tired. ". But Peng says the body doesn't feel much when it's involved.

The number of people who added him to Wechat increased every day until "the number was no longer prompted and became a small red dot. ". He responds carefully to every request. Old Peng made it his job to do the good work.

Bai Han, too, had only "half-slept for two hours" since last night. During those days, Baehan, a theater actor, took on various tasks, including media editing and copywriting. Early this morning, the design in the drawing, he was afraid that the copywriting can not keep up with the midnight sleep wake up insist on the platform copywriting out.

On the 26th, there was a lot of traffic on the site. The site's been blocked. After tencent saw what they were doing, it also found them and provided them with domain name support.

It's not easy to do a good deed. Even if each of them does not participate in any money, material operation, only participate in the construction of the information platform itself, the query still followed.

Someone took their poster and altered it as propaganda for their own fund-raising. Others added to their core members' wechat, pulled them into a group to discuss with him "what's next" and tried to bring them into commercial operation. Their core members had to emphasize in the group, "we do not touch money, do not touch things. ". The other side replies immediately, "that we are not going the same way" .

They felt helpless, Bai said. "there is no way. There are all kinds of people. ". At the same time, they are more worried about being misunderstood and don't want to spoil a good thing.

But more people and events moved them. Over the past few days, hospital staff who have received donations have thanked them on wechat. One of the volunteers was touched by a voice from a doctor saying, "I thank you for your efforts on behalf of my fellow doctors. ".


In the interview, Baehan mentioned the word "cohesion" three times to me, which was his biggest feeling these days. All of us, in one word, are cohesive.

But Old Peng feels, at the beginning of this matter, they thought, this matter is likely to have no result, or will suddenly stop. "If the epidemic is over and we are over, that's what we want to do. It doesn't matter if we do it first, " he said

Someone took their poster and altered it as propaganda for their own fund-raising. Others added to their core members' wechat, pulled them into a group to discuss with him "what's next" and tried to bring them into commercial operation. Their core members had to emphasize in the group, "we do not touch money, do not touch things. ". The other side replies immediately, "that we are not going the same way" .

They felt helpless, Bai said. "there is no way. There are all kinds of people. ". At the same time, they are more worried about being misunderstood and don't want to spoil a good thing.
